591
00:29:51,740 --> 00:29:52,980
If my parents were alive,

592
00:29:53,460 --> 00:29:54,740
they would also prepare...

593
00:29:58,860 --> 00:29:59,700
The thank-you gifts.

594
00:30:00,220 --> 00:30:01,100
I'm just doing this

595
00:30:01,100 --> 00:30:01,940
for my parents.

596
00:30:04,820 --> 00:30:05,980
What if I ask you

597
00:30:06,700 --> 00:30:07,940
for a divorce paper?

598
00:30:08,500 --> 00:30:09,740
Then, as the former Mrs. Wei,

599
00:30:10,340 --> 00:30:11,220
she still deserves

600
00:30:11,220 --> 00:30:12,060
all these things.

601
00:30:15,260 --> 00:30:16,460
Thank you, Young Marquis

602
00:30:16,460 --> 00:30:17,300
for your generosity.

603
00:30:18,140 --> 00:30:19,100
But I don't think

604
00:30:20,220 --> 00:30:21,340
she wants the paper now.

605
00:30:26,140 --> 00:30:27,340
What are they talking about?

606
00:30:34,420 --> 00:30:35,260
Are you sure?

607
00:30:45,980 --> 00:30:46,900
My brother is right.

608
00:30:47,700 --> 00:30:48,660
I need to think it over.

609
00:30:52,500 --> 00:30:54,100
Stop talking in riddles.

610
00:30:54,260 --> 00:30:55,940
I don't understand.

611
00:30:57,180 --> 00:30:58,580
It's getting late.

612
00:30:58,940 --> 00:30:59,940
Your Lordship,

613
00:31:00,100 --> 00:31:01,340
